Effortless. Elegant. Ever-evolving.
Nriti Shah, the voice behind @balsamicfinegear, brings her signature blend of mindful living and refined style to Timeless Faces of PRJ.

With every frame, she reminds us that true beauty lies in authenticity—and that jewellery, like life, is best when worn with intention.

#TimelessFacesOfPRJ #PrithvirajJewels #GraceInEveryMoment #StyleWithSubstance

Yes, it might change your life.

5 minutes of this wooden wonder =
✅ Reduced puffiness

✅ Mood instantly lifted (because it feels so good)

Basically, it’s like a mini spa appointment — minus the price tag and questionable spa music.
Science says yes. My abs say thank you. 💁🏽‍♀️

Save this for your next bloated morning.
Or better yet, send it to that one friend who’s always googling “how to debloat fast.”

#LymphaticDrainage #WellnessHack #BloatBeGone #EverydayRituals #RealNotRetouched

This was taken the night my “blog” went live. 2013. 
Newly married. In a new city. No real plan, but so much hope. I still remember this evening. I had dragged my laptop to a bar in Mumbai to show my closest girlfriends what I’d been building. It wasn’t meant to be a blog, or an Instagram page, or anything public really. It was supposed to be a small, curated e-commerce site. I had called it Balsamic Finegear — a name that was a twist on the salad dressing (balsamic) and fine, beautiful things (gear). Clothes, accessories, statement pieces — things I loved collecting and styling.
But building an actual e-comm platform felt like too much at the time. I didn’t have a team, I didn’t know anyone in fashion or tech, and honestly, I didn’t even have that much confidence. What I did have was time — a lot of it. I was in a new marriage, a new city, had left behind my old life and friends, and was looking for something to pour myself into. I’d always been told that I had great personal style — strangers would stop and ask me where something was from or how I’d put it together. So instead of selling products, I started sharing outfits. I followed international bloggers who were just beginning to shape this strange new world of digital style. And something clicked. I had a background in journalism, and the idea of writing about fashion & not just wearing it, lit something up in me. I started a blog to post outfit breakdowns, moodboards, shopping tips, and little journal-style entries about life and style. Back then, it wasn’t about algorithms, aesthetics or “engagement.” It was about expressing yourself. Owning your voice. 
Influencing wasn’t even a profession in India yet — not in the way it is now. There were barely any Indian content creators in this space. And then, just as it all started gaining momentum, life shifted again.  Continued in comments.

latestPosts.caption:
Every morning like clockwork, my mum starts her day with a quiet ritual of self-care — not for the ‘gram, not for trends — just for herself.
Black garlic for its antioxidant & anti inflammatory properties, neem water for detoxification, methi seed water for blood sugar control, soaked almonds & walnuts for the brain, sesame seeds for calcium & cholesterol control, a spoon of ghee for her joints, and that magical mix of age-old Ayurvedic wisdom and modern discipline.

She’s 60 and radiant, but more importantly, she feels & looks 50 — strong, sharp, energetic, grounded & gorgeous. 
And while I was busy chasing superfood fads, she was quietly sipping on things passed down by her mother and grandmother.

It’s not just about looking good — it’s about aging with grace, energy, and vitality.
Wellness isn’t a phase in our home. It’s our love language, our inheritance, our jam.
And this reel? It’s a tiny glimpse into the powerhouse of habits that built the woman I call Mom 💛🧿🧿🧿

#WellnessIsOurJam #AyurvedaMeetsEveryday #SuperfoodRoutine #RootedInTradition #HealthyAtEveryAge #MorningRituals #StrongWomenStrongHabits
